default5. defaultLack of effectiveness of national idefaultnitiatives to help aid economic defaultrecovery defaultUlster Bank has a strong record
default of participation in incentive schemes that the Government has made available to all UK
default licensed banks. In particular, the bank has embraced the Bank of England’s Funding for Lending Scheme (FLS), lending £100 million to more than 650 customers since it was launched in mid-September 2012. The FLS is a good method of providing affordable fina
defaultnce to businesses across Northern Ireland.
defaultAlth
defaultough all
default the
default main lenders in N
defaultorthern 
defaultI
defaultreland
default participate in the Enterprise Finance Guarantee scheme
default (EFG)
